grandmaster in 1984. However, he only scored occasional successes against the
main Soviet players.} 1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 Nf6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. e5 d5 6. Bb5
{White regains the pawn.} Ne4 7. Nxd4 Bd7 8. Bxc6 bxc6 9. O-O Be7 (9... Bc5 {
