Rxb8 25. Nxb8 a5 26. Nd7 {brings no relief.}) 21. Rxd7 Bd6 22. Bxa7 Rxc2 23. a4
$1 {Estrin advances his distant passed pawn.} Rc6 24. a5 Ra6 25. Bd4 Rfa8 26.
g4 h6 27. Kf2 $1 {
White can sacrifice a valuable pawn, because the restriction increases.} Rxa5
28. Rxa5 Rxa5 29. Ke3 Ra8 30. h4 Bg3 $5 31. g5 $1 Rf8 32. e7 Re8 33. g6 $1 {
Black will be mated soon.   The star of the tournament was the 17-years-old
